From 0e0f98c165238437d907d2391adc10a8ef40c30f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ashish Kumar Singh <ashishkmr472@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 21 May 2026 14:25:26 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] nvkms/nvidia-drm: enable Wayland DRM-lease of VR HMDs

Make NVIDIA-driven VR HMDs leasable and presentable over wp_drm_lease on Wayland
(the kernel equivalent of the X11 "xrandr --set non-desktop 1" + Xorg flip-
permission path):

- Flag the HMD's native (largest-area) timing as RandR-preferred so preferred-
  only mode scans (SteamVR's vrcompositor) select it.  [nvkms-modepool.c]
- Expose the existing isVrHmd device bit to DRM as connector non_desktop=1, so
  the compositor advertises the HMD over wp_drm_lease and keeps it out of desktop
  atomic commits.  [nvkms-kapi.h x2, nvkms-kapi.c, nvidia-drm-connector.c]
- Grant a DRM lessee flip permission on its leased head: per-apiHead
  lesseeFlipPermissive, set at CREATE_LEASE and cleared at REVOKE_LEASE, honored
  in nvCheckLayerPermissions().  [nvkms-api.h, nvkms-types.h, nvkms.c,
  nvkms-flip.c, nvidia-drm-drv.c]

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
